    <section id="recipe-details">
        <h2>Recipe Details</h2>
        <p><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 20 minutes</p>
        <p><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 20 minutes</p>
        <p><strong>Total Time:</strong> 40 minutes</p>
    </section>

    <section id="ingredients">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 Box of pasta</li>
            <li>1 Tablespoon olive oil</li>
            <li>1 Chicken breast</li>
            <li>1 Tablespoon flour</li>
            <li>1 Tablespoon butter</li>
            <li>3 Garlic cloves finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 Tablespoon fresh rosemary roughly chopped</li>
            <li>3/4 Cup heavy cream</li>
            <li>1 Teaspoon pepper</li>
            <li>1 Tablespoon lemon juice</li>
            <li>50 Grams parmesan cheese gated</li>
            <li>Lemon zest and roemary to finish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="instructions">
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Cook pasta in saltted water, under cook the pasta by 1 minute. save 1/4 cup of pasta water.</li>
            <li>Flatten chick breast, season with salt and pepperon both sides then dust with flour.</li>
            <li>Heat olive oil in pan medium - high heat, fry chciken until cooked all the way through. Wrap in tin foil and set aside.</li>
            <li>Heat butter in same pan on medium heatand gently fry garlic (should not brown). Add rosemary and cook for 30 seconds.</li>
            <li>Pour in cream and bring to simmer (not boiling). Slowly add parmasean in 2-3 batches allowing it to melt. Add pepper and lemon quickly.</li>
            <li>Add 1/4 cup pasta water and let simmer for 2-3 minutes to thicken.</li> 
            <li>Slice chicken into slices and add both chicken and pasta to your sauce and mix.</li>
            <li>Dish plates and top with rosemary and lemon zest and serve.</li>

        </ol>
    </section>
